@Jasmine Rice{150%grams} Boil a half-full #kettle{}. Pour it into a #saucepan{} with @salt{1/4%tsp} on high heat.

Boil the rice, ~{12-13%minutes}.

Once cooked, drain, pop back in the #pan{} and cover.

Meanwhile, heat a drizzle of oil in a saucepan on medium-high heat.

Once hot, fry the @Thai Green Style Paste{45%grams} and @Thai Style Spice Mix{1%sachet} (add less if you'd prefer things milder), ~{30%secs}.

Stir in the @Coconut Milk{180%milliliter} and @Chicken Stock Paste{10%grams}.

Add the @Diced British Chicken Breast{240%grams}. Bring to the boil, then lower the heat. Simmer, ~{10-12%minutes}.

> IMPORTANT: Wash hands and utensils after handling raw meat. Cook so there's no pink in the middle.

Meanwhile, halve the @Lime{1}.

Once thickened, add the @Baby Spinach{40%grams} in handfuls, making sure it's piping hot, ~{1-2%mins}.

Squeeze in some lime juice. Add a splash of water if it's too thick.

Taste and season with salt, @ground black pepper{} and more lime juice if needed.

Fluff up the rice and share between your bowls.

Top with the curry.

Cut any remaining lime into wedges for squeezing over.

Enjoy!